This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques applied to text data. Specifically, it focuses on the interpretability of topic models, which is a common problem in computational linguistics and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). However, the paper also uses quantitative evaluation methods and statistical models, which are typical of machine learning research. Therefore, it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and text classification, which are relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are relevant to cs.DL (Deep Learning).
